         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>Outsourcing of Daycare Service and lease of Hafan Deg Centre in Rhyl</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="85312100"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Denbighshire County Council is seeking an innovative and a progressive partner with the expertise and proven track record in working older people aged 65+ and vulnerable adults who require assistance and support to manage essential activities of daily living. There are two parts to this tender:</P>
               <P>The chosen provider will:</P>
               <P>1) Take on, in its entirety, the Hafan Deg Day Centre building, situated in Rhyl, through a 25 years lease with Denbighshire County Council.</P>
               <P>2) Run and transform this well-established and valued center into an innovative and energetic hub for the local community and surrounding area through a 3 years contract with the option to extend for a further 2 years.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="85312100"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="85300000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKL13"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Hafan Deg Day Centre Rhyl.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Partners will provide a focus not only on the quality of care, but also on Welsh language and culture, and will continue to nurture positive relationships with the local community.</P>
                  <P>Partners must be able to demonstrate their:</P>
                  <P>1) experience in the delivery of quality support services, in a particular innovative service and change management experience, and/or,</P>
                  <P>2) experience in engaging local communities, and/or,</P>
                  <P>3) experience of managing buildings for social care enterprises,</P>
                  <P>4) experience in achieving outcomes for service users in line with the Social Services, and Well Being (Wales) Act 2014.</P>
                  <P>Partners will demonstrate a clear vision for the development of the center as a community facility, with a focus on promoting independence and well-being. They will provide a wider range of activities for the local community, to develop the potential and promote the independence, choice, and control of service users.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
